<header>
<div id="instruction">
	In the previous exercise we saw that Alexandra didn't really pay attention to the topic in Phase 2. Which of the following would you suggest to improve Alexandra's performance?
</div>
</header>
	
<section id="body">
  <img class="rightFloat" src="../media/set6_05.jpg" mode="1" id="1001"/>
  <ol id="targetspotting">
		<list class="answerList">
        <li><a id="t1">Talk more about the subject in general.</a></li>
	    <li><a id="t2">Read the instructions carefully.</a></li>
        <li><a id="t3">Find out what to expect in each part of the test.</a></li>
        <li><a id="t4">Ask the examiner for more information.</a></li>
	    <li><a id="t5">Learn more about advertising and other popular topics.</a></li>
        <li><a id="t6">Consider taking notes to sort out her thoughts.</a></li></list>
	</ol>
  
  <p class="linespace"></p>
</section>

<section id="fb1">
  <p class="feedbacktext">Speaking more generally would not help.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb2">
  <p class="feedbacktext">Yes. You will never answer the question correctly unless you read the instructions carefully.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb3">
  <p class="feedbacktext">This will help you to prepare properly, and will increase your confidence.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb4">
  <p class="feedbacktext">She had all the information she needed on the card.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb5">
  <p class="feedbacktext">Her knowledge was not the problem here.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb6">
  <p class="feedbacktext">Notes will help you to keep going, and will also prevent you from straying from the topic.
  </p>
